Product Requirements Document (PRD)
Project: macOS Portfolio Experience
Owner: Huzaifa Sajid
Tech Stack: Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion
1. Project Overview

Build a highly interactive portfolio website that simulates a real macOS desktop experience inside the browser.

The portfolio should feel like:

A lightweight macOS clone
Interactive desktop operating system
Personal portfolio integrated into the OS
Smooth animations and realistic UI behavior
Modern, cinematic, premium experience

The website is NOT a normal portfolio.

The entire portfolio itself IS the operating system.

Users should feel:

“I am using Huzaifa’s computer.”

2. Core Goals
Primary Goals
Create unforgettable portfolio experience
Showcase frontend engineering skills
Demonstrate advanced UI/UX engineering
Demonstrate system design thinking
Make portfolio highly interactive
Secondary Goals
Increase recruiter engagement time
Stand out among traditional portfolios
Make projects feel immersive
Showcase animation and architecture skills
3. Technical Constraints
Requirements
No Authentication
No Database
Static portfolio data
Fully frontend application
Responsive for desktop-first
Mobile support optional (reduced mode)
4. Technology Stack
Core Framework
Next.js App Router
TypeScript
Styling
Tailwind CSS
Animation
Framer Motion
State Management

Choose one:

Zustand (recommended)
OR
Context API
Icons
Lucide React
macOS style custom icons
Drag/Resize
react-rnd
OR
interact.js
Sound Effects (Optional)
use-sound
5. High Level User Experience

When user opens website:

macOS boot-like animation
Desktop appears
Dock animates in
Top menu bar visible
Floating desktop icons visible
Cursor interactions feel realistic
Windows open like macOS
Portfolio content lives inside folders/apps
